    "source_sections": {
      "references": "",
      "remarks": "A problem of Deshouillers and Erd\\H{o}s (an infinite version of [874]). Such sets are sometimes called admissible. Erd\\H{o}s writes 'it [is not] completely trivial to find such a sequence for which $a_{n+1}/a_n\\to 1$'. It is not clear from this whether Deshouillers and Erd\\H{o}s knew of such a sequence."
    },
